## Custom Error Messages
Override `messages()` to provide user-friendly error messages instead of Laravel's defaults:
```php
public function messages(): array
{
    return [
        'title.required'      => 'Please provide a title for your post.',
        'content.required'    => 'The content cannot be empty.',
        'category_id.exists'  => 'Please select a valid category.',
    ];
}
```

## Authorization
